<item>
            <title>[SPR-19] OracleLobHandler has invalid constant</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-19</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In OracleLobHandler, it assumes the constant&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DURATION_SESSION=10&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In the classes12.zip that I have (from Oracle 9i) dated &lt;br/&gt;
4/26/2002, the constant is actually&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BLOB.DURATION_SESSION=1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you pass &apos;10&apos; into BLOB.createTemporary, it will cause &lt;br/&gt;
an exception (reporting invalid argument).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like you will unfortunately need to use reflection &lt;br/&gt;
and access the value of this field to be compatible...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Like clazz.getField( &quot;DURATION_SESSION&quot; ) where clazz &lt;br/&gt;
is Oracle&apos;s BLOB class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, wouldn&apos;t it be better to be dynamically loading &lt;br/&gt;
using Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader() &lt;br/&gt;
instead of Class.forName()??&lt;/p&gt;</description>
